### Description

I want to lazy-load a block only if the user has permission, and reactively show/hide it if permissions change.
Currently requires:

```html
@defer (when hasPermission) {
  @if (hasPermission) {
    <admin-panel/>
  }
}
```

### Proposed solution

Add a new syntax to the defer block:

```html
@defer (if hasPermission) {
  <admin-panel/>
}
```
Lazy-loads on first true
Reactively shows/hides afterwards

### Alternatives considered

* Keep the current pattern (@defer + @if) but duplicates the condition.


* Introduce a separate block

```html
@if lazy(prefetch on condition) (hasPermission) {
  <admin-panel />
}
```
Solves the problem, but introduces a completely new syntax.
Problematic when describing @else / @else if branches: it’s unclear how these blocks would attach to a @if lazy, how fallbacks or prefetching would propagate, and whether they should also be lazy-loaded. This creates ambiguity in template structure.

